    "We empirically find that the labeling functions can perfectly fit the training data, leading to small training errors.",
    "In parallel, f original achieves a small test error, indicating good learning performance, and quantified by a small generalization gap gen(f original) = small.",
    "On the contrary, the randomization process causes f corrupted to achieve a large test error, which in turn results in a large generalization gap gen(f corrupted) = large.",
